<h2 id="sec-2" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">The ecosystem: 4 ways to shop & sell</h2>

<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-03.png" alt="" style="width:100%; display:block; margin:1.5em 0; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);" />

<p style="line-height:1.7; color:#2d3748;">TikTok Shop has four touchpoints where shoppers find and buy products — and each one is a different doorway for you to earn. <strong>Shoppable Videos</strong> are normal TikToks with a product link attached. <strong>Shop Page</strong> is a dedicated shopping tab inside the app where people browse like they would on Amazon. <strong>Live Shopping</strong> is where you sell during a LIVE stream in real time. And the <strong>Shop Tab</strong> on your profile is where your followers can browse everything you've ever tagged. You don't have to pick one — most creators end up using all four as they grow.</p>

<div style="margin:1.8em 0; padding:1.2em 1.5em; background:#f7f9fc; border-radius:12px; border:1px solid #e3e8ef;">
  <p style="font-weight:600; margin:0 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">Quick check: What's the main way creators earn on TikTok Shop?</p>
  <details style="margin:0.3em 0; padding:0.5em 0.8em; background:#fff; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #e3e8ef; cursor:pointer;"><summary>A) Commissions from shoppable videos and live sales</summary><p style="margin:0.5em 0 0 0; color:#2f855a;">✓ Correct. You create content with product links and earn a cut of every sale.</p></details>
  <details style="margin:0.3em 0; padding:0.5em 0.8em; background:#fff; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #e3e8ef; cursor:pointer;"><summary>B) Subscription fees from fans</summary><p style="margin:0.5em 0 0 0; color:#c53030;">✗ Nope — that's different platforms. TikTok Shop is all about product sales.</p></details>
  <details style="margin:0.3em 0; padding:0.5em 0.8em; background:#fff; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #e3e8ef; cursor:pointer;"><summary>C) Ad revenue share</summary><p style="margin:0.5em 0 0 0; color:#c53030;">✗ That's YouTube. Shop earnings come from affiliate commissions.</p></details>
  <details style="margin:0.3em 0; padding:0.5em 0.8em; background:#fff; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #e3e8ef; cursor:pointer;"><summary>D) Selling your own inventory</summary><p style="margin:0.5em 0 0 0; color:#c53030;">✗ You don't need your own products — that's the beauty of the affiliate model.</p></details>
</div>

<h2 id="sec-3" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">How you get paid: the 4 revenue models</h2>

<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-04.png" alt="" style="width:100%; display:block; margin:1.5em 0; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);" />

<p style="line-height:1.7; color:#2d3748;">There are four ways to actually put money in your bank from TikTok Shop — and they're stackable. The <strong>Affiliate Model</strong> is performance-based: you add a product link to a video and earn 5–20% commission when people buy. No inventory, no shipping, no faff. The <strong>UGC Model</strong> is retainer-based: brands pay you a flat fee (usually £50–£200+ per video) to create content for them, and you get paid whether or not the video sells anything. The <strong>Hybrid Model</strong> is the best of both worlds — a flat creation fee <em>plus</em> commission on sales. And <strong>Live Shopping</strong> is real-time selling during a broadcast, where you earn commission on every sale made while you're live.</p>

<h2 id="sec-4" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">Performance vs. retainer — pick your lane</h2>

<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-05.png" alt="" style="width:100%; display:block; margin:1.5em 0; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);" />

<p style="line-height:1.7; color:#2d3748;">Here's the important distinction most people miss. When you do <strong>Affiliate (Performance)</strong>, you're the salesperson — your income varies based on how many people actually buy. The ceiling is unlimited (a single viral video could pay rent), but you only eat what you kill. When you do <strong>UGC (Retainer)</strong>, you're the content creator — brands pay you a fixed fee per deliverable, and you're paid for the <em>asset</em>, not the outcome. Start with Affiliate because you can do it today, by yourself, with no gatekeepers. Upgrade to UGC retainer deals once you've built a portfolio — that's what agency connections like Creator Scans unlock.</p>

<h2 id="sec-5" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">Who can get behind the wheel?</h2>

