</div>

<h2 id="sec-8" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">Choose your lane: independent vs. Creator Scans</h2>

<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-09.png" alt="" style="width:100%; display:block; margin:1.5em 0; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);" />

<p style="line-height:1.7; color:#2d3748;">Here's the side-by-side. Going <strong>Independent (unbound)</strong> gets you standard commission rates, no TAP access, no support if things go wrong, and you're navigating violations and contracts on your own. Flexible, but solo. Going <strong>Bound to Creator Scans</strong> gets you higher commissions via TAP, exclusive brand deals and retainers, violation support and strategy, and a structured growth path. You give up some flexibility in exchange for significantly more support and earning power. Most of our creators bind once they understand the maths — but we'll never push you into it.</p>

<h2 id="sec-9" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">Avoiding the crash: bans & violations</h2>

<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-10.png" alt="" style="width:100%; display:block; margin:1.5em 0; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);" />

<p style="line-height:1.7; color:#2d3748;">Before we go any further, I need to say this clearly: <strong>TikTok Shop policies are strict.</strong> Misleading claims, hidden disclosures, promoting prohibited products — any of these can get your Shop banned, sometimes without warning. This is one of the biggest reasons creators bind to an agency. When you're with Creator Scans, we provide violation support and help you navigate the appeals process if something goes sideways. We'll cover exactly <em>how</em> to avoid bans and stay compliant in Lesson 2 — for now, just know the guardrails exist and they matter.</p>

<h2 id="sec-10" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">The driver's seat philosophy</h2>

<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-11.png" alt="" style="width:100%; display:block; margin:1.5em 0; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);" />

<p style="line-height:1.7; color:#2d3748;">Here's how Creator Scans teaches differently. The old way is <strong>Theory → Action</strong>: sit in a classroom for months learning every possible detail, <em>then</em> go out and try it. Our way is <strong>Action → Coaching</strong>: you get behind the wheel first, we watch how you drive, and <em>then</em> we coach you on the specific things that'll make you better. When you learn to drive a car, you don't sit and watch a driving instructor drive the car first — you get in and go, and the instructor says "tilt to the side slightly" after they've seen what you actually do. Same principle here.</p>

<h2 id="sec-11" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">Why we need to see you drive</h2>

<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-12.png" alt="" style="width:100%; display:block; margin:1.5em 0; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);" />

<p style="line-height:1.7; color:#2d3748;">Success on TikTok Shop isn't just technical. It depends on things we literally can't teach you in a vacuum: your <strong>communication style</strong> (how you naturally talk to a camera), your <strong>audience connection</strong> (how in tune you are with who's watching), and your <strong>value articulation</strong> (how clearly you can explain why something is worth buying). Some people have these naturally. Others need guidance. We can't know which one you are until you start creating — that's why we have to see you in action before we can give you the <em>right</em> advice for <em>you</em>.</p>

