<h2 id="sec-12" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">The reality check: input vs. output</h2>

<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-13.png" alt="" style="width:100%; display:block; margin:1.5em 0; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);" />

<p style="line-height:1.7; color:#2d3748;">This graph is the single most important slide in this lesson. Your <strong>input</strong> (showing up, posting consistently, improving) is a flat, steady line from day one. Your <strong>output</strong> (actual sales) is basically zero for the first few months… and then it starts curving up steeply around month 6–9. Most people quit in month 2 because they're looking at the output line and panicking. Don't be most people. <strong>Commit to a 6–9 month horizon. Trust the process.</strong> Focus on the input — the output is lagging behind, but it's coming.</p>

<h2 id="sec-13" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">Your one action item</h2>

<img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-14.png" alt="" style="width:100%; display:block; margin:1.5em 0; border-radius:8px; box-shadow:0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);" />

<p style="line-height:1.7; color:#2d3748;">You don't need to film anything yet. Your homework from Lesson 1 is to <strong>start observing</strong>. Open TikTok, scroll, and notice: what <em>categories</em> are you naturally drawn to? What <em>stops your scroll</em>? What would you actually spend money on if someone showed it to you in the right way? Screenshot anything that catches you. We're going to use these observations to pick your first products in Lesson 2 — so the more honest you are with yourself about what you actually like, the better your starting point will be.</p>

<h2 id="sec-14" style="font-size:1.5em; font-weight:700; margin:2.5em 0 0.6em 0; color:#1a202c;">What you walk away with</h2>

